**Event Title:** CON - CTF Blue Team Style

**Event Overview:**
A cyber competition designed for participants to enhance their blue team skills through digital forensics, network forensics, malware analysis, hashing/encryption, and other areas of cybersecurity. 

**Objectives:**
- Analyze cyber-attack data to identify vulnerabilities and mitigate threats.
- Participants will unravel various aspects of a cyber-attack by solving challenges.

**Game Format:**
- **Team or Solo:** Play individually or in teams (2-4 members).
- **Online Access:** Game available through an online portal.
- **Compatible Tools:** Suggested tools include the SANS SIFT Workstation.
- **Scoring:** Real-time scoreboard to track progress.

**Rules of Engagement:**
- No attempts to disrupt other players or the scoreboard.
- Dynamic scoring based on challenge difficulty.

**Participation:**
- Open to all skill levels, from beginners to professionals.

**Schedule:**
- **Monday:** Closed
- **Tuesday:** 12:00 PM - 5:00 PM
- **Wednesday:** 9:00 AM - 5:00 PM
- **Thursday:** 9:00 AM - 5:00 PM
- **Friday:** 9:00 AM - 11:00 AM

**Organizer Contact:**
- Official Website: [SAINTCON](https://saintcon.org)

**Social Media Sharing (Open Graph):**
- Twitter and Facebook tags set for promotion with proper images and description about the event.

**Visuals:**
- Includes various graphics related to the event to enhance engagement. 

**Conclusion:**
Encourages participants to take part in a competitive, educational environment focusing on cybersecurity defense practices.